Today we will be working with curiosity
-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

keep your curiosity its important to keep evolving throughout your life
its one of the few things that we as humans are the only beings able to do when it comes to making progress in the world

its dangerous to take children's ability to be curios

one of the things we can do to make our own curiosity better is by breaking out daily routines and trying new things and by that expanding what we might be interested in and then making our whole experience more interesting

How do we keep our curiosity
    always ask open ended questions to keep a conversation going
    keep talking about what sparks interest and ti might just lead to more things that will spark interest later

    trying new things is one of the best ways to make yourself more curious 
------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

The 4 I in curiosity

Identity
    Self reflection

    Appreciate questions
    
    Share your curiosity 

Incitement
    Acknowledge
        Getting acknowledged for what you do
    Reward
        Being rewarded for what you do
    Positive incitement
        Make something positive to strive for to help motivate you to be curious 
Iteration
    Learning by doing
        You can more often than not learn a lot about what you are doing by doing it
    Innovation
        Find new, better, smarter ways to do the tasks you have
    Learn by failing
        You can learn a lot by failing so don't be afraid of failing
    Supportive environment
        Your environment is important for how you can evolve your skills
    Open and transparent workspaces
        Being open and transparent is important and sparks conversation and interest in what you are working on

Intersection
    More perspective
    
    Combine knowledge
    
    Do recherche and experiments

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

curiosity is the future of the world

it will be one of the most important things to further what will be possible in the future

